%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 55fc01baa0be7b54e8ef6801bfc93ce6, type: 3}
  m_Name: SheepThree
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  PromptOneButtonDisplay: 0
  PromptTwoButtonDisplay: 1
  ButtonOneText: Somewhat
  ButtonTwoText: No
  NormalDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I bet that gun feels pretty liberating right now.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: This game being one-player, I'm sure it's more relieving now. You don't
      have to worry about others shooting back at you.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Yeah I mean, you're right about that.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Better yet, someone isn't controlling the game for you, where someone
      is winning and you're losing.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Even though this is still a casino first and foremost, do you feel in
      control right now?
  ButtonOneDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Not completely.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: I get to shoot anyone without consequence. That's nice.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: I can treat this casino as my personal rage room and relieve some 'inner
      turmoil.'
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Wow, me caring for myself? Crazy. Maybe next round I should shoot myself.
      Disgusting to care for myself.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Anyways, I don't feel completely in control because this is a casino.
      I'm not hosting this game; it's you.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: The people I get to shoot are under your control with your shuffling.
      That binds me to you, doesn't it?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Yes.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: "Great\u2026"
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They grasp their arm. Their arm is horribly torn up. Parts of their
      flesh are exposed and red from the brute force of wool being ripped off.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They tear a larger chunk of wool than they intended, higher up their
      arm, and hand the clump over.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: The creature takes it wordlessly.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: ...I'll shuffle a new round now.
  ButtonTwoDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Even in this game, we're never allowed full control over anything because
      of lies.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: In the end, everything is inherently unjust. There will always be someone
      who lies, someone who controls more than you do.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: I can say I enjoy this game because I have more freedom of choice, but
      it's not a complete choice.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: And it can be taken away at any time. Choice ends up being an illusion.
      It always does.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: People are cruel and make you feel you have to rely on them to make
      choices for you for whatever reasons.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: To summarize it for your stupid little brain hearing me say this, if
      it weren't obvious to you, I hate people. And I hate you too.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Whatever, I don't even know why I'm answering your stupid questions.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: 'I don''t matter to you anyway. '
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They grasp their arm. Their arm is horribly torn up. Parts of their
      flesh are exposed and red from the brute force of wool being ripped off.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They tear a larger chunk of wool than they intended, higher up their
      arm, and hand the clump over.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: The creature takes it wordlessly.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: ...I'll shuffle a new round now.
